text: Dionne may refer to: *Dionne (name) * Centre Marcel Dionne, a multi-purpose arena in Quebec, Canada * Dionne Lake in Nunavut, Canada * Dionne quintuplets, the first quintuplets known to have survived their infancy * USS Dionne (DE-261), a destroyer escort ship of the United States Navy during World War II *"Dionne", song by Prince Crystal Ball (box set) ==See also== *Dion (disambiguation) *Dione (disambiguation)
